{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "I have enough context to make the changes without fighting the current scaffold. The implementation plan is: 1. Replace the loose env reader with a validated settings loader that builds a nested config object, discovers `secrets.yaml`, m...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_31", "text": "I have enough context to make the changes without fighting the current scaffold. The implementation plan is:\n\n1. Replace the loose env reader with a validated settings loader that builds a nested config object, discovers `secrets.yaml`, merges `defaults < secrets.yaml < environment`, and emits a single readable error message when required values are missing or malformed.\n2. Keep the current app/service code stable by adapting the health and startup paths to the new settings shape rather than rewriting unrelated modules.\n3. Add a root `secrets.example.yaml` plus docs in the repo and backend README that explain discovery, precedence, Docker Compose behavior, and the fact that Gemini credentials stay backend-only.\n4. Expand backend tests to cover secrets-file loading, env override behavior, missing-config failures, and the startup error path from `python -m app`.\n5. Run the backend test suite and targeted startup checks, then checkpoint the code in git before writing the final reviewer summary file.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 63, "prompt_index": 6, "prompt_name": "05 \u2014 Backend Settings, Env Loading, and `secrets.yaml` Support", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T21:42:47-07:00"}
